Materialize the v2 web app under apps/web (legacy app under apps stays untouched
per the Phase 0 coexistence contract — full deletion lands in a later sub-PR).

Stack: Next.js 15.0.3 App Router · React 19 RC · TanStack Query 5 ·
TailwindCSS dark palette · @gv/api-client + @gv/types via workspace.

Chrome:
  - RootLayout → Providers (QueryClient + AuthProvider)
  - (app) layout → AuthGate + Sidebar + TopBar + main grid
  - (auth) layout → centered login form
  - Sidebar: 14 sections, role-filtered, stub badges; ALL_HREFS export
  - TopBar: env badge + user roles + sign-out
  - AuthGate: redirects unauthenticated to /login
  - Token lifecycle: localStorage (gv.accessToken/refreshToken/accessExpiresAt)
  - api singleton wraps @gv/api-client with mutable tokenGetter closure

Functional pages (wired to control plane):
  - /login                 — email/password sign-in
  - /overview              — landing cards (control plane status, roles, links)
  - /market/symbols        — filterable Phase 0 watchlist
  - /ops/health            — /ready + /live probes with dep checks
  - /ops/flags             — list + admin-gated PATCH toggle
  - /admin/system          — admin-gated inline JSON CRUD on KV store

Stub pages (60 total) — each renders <ToDoBanner title=... phase=... />:
  Command(1) replay
  Market(5) watchlist levels regimes sessions liquidity
  Intelligence(7) fusion structure flow setups recall agents calibration
  Strategies(5) catalog builder active promotions dna
  Quant Lab(5) backtests replay experiments metrics ranking
  Execution(5) orders fills positions risk killswitch
  Portfolio(5) pnl exposure correlation allocation drawdown
  Operations(7) slos alerts incidents deployments latency feeds logs
  Audit(3) events kv-changes exports
  Governance(4) trust approvals demotions policies
  Learning(3) feedback missed drift
  Research(2) brainstorm regimes
  Admin(5) users roles api-keys webhooks mcp
  Settings(3) profile preferences api-tokens

Each stub names its scheduled phase + describes the planned feature so
sidebar drill-downs show real intent rather than a 404.

